1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:04,600
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:10,980
My name is Catherine and today we're talking about where people come from or nationalities.
我是Catherine，今天我们讨论的是人们来自哪里，或者说国籍。

4
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:11,980
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:11,980 --> 00:00:15,880
Many people come from many different countries just like our listeners and there are specific
很多人来自许多不同的国家，就像我们的听众一样，而且有一些特定的

6
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:20,200
words or adjectives and nouns to describe people.
词语、形容词和名词来描述这些人。

7
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:23,320
Like for example, somebody who is from China.
比如，有人来自中国。

8
00:00:23,320 --> 00:00:25,440
A Chinese person.
一个中国人。

9
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:26,440
That's right.
没错。

10
00:00:26,440 --> 00:00:29,360
So in your case, Marco, you are an Ecuadorian.
所以就拿你来说，Marco，你是一个厄瓜多尔人。

11
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:30,360
That's right.
没错。

12
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:32,720
So that means I come from the country Ecuador.
这意味着我来自厄瓜多尔这个国家。

13
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:35,200
I, on the other hand, am an American.
而我呢，是一个美国人。

14
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,960
I come from America.
我来自美国。

15
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:37,960
That's right.
没错。

16
00:00:37,960 --> 00:00:38,960
So we have a lot of these examples.
所以我们有很多这样的例子。

17
00:00:38,960 --> 00:00:40,600
Why don't we jump into the dialogue.
我们不如直接进入对话吧。

18
00:00:40,600 --> 00:00:45,760
Let's see where all of the people from this international class are from and we'll be
让我们看看这个国际班里的所有人都来自哪里，然后我们会

19
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:55,600
back to talk about it.
回来讨论。

20
00:00:55,600 --> 00:00:57,160
Hey how was your first day of class?
嘿，你第一天上课怎么样？

21
00:00:57,160 --> 00:00:59,960
I'm a level two and I'm loving my class this semester.
我是二级班，这学期我很喜欢我的课。

22
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:03,720
It's great being in a class of international students.
在一个国际学生班里真是太棒了。

23
00:01:03,720 --> 00:01:08,020
Mine was okay except that no one in my class speaks English.
我的课还行，只是班上没人说英语。

24
00:01:08,020 --> 00:01:12,480
I guess it will force me to converse in Chinese more in class so at least I should improve
我想这会逼我在课上多说中文，所以至少这学期我应该能

25
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:14,340
a lot this semester.
进步很多。

26
00:01:14,340 --> 00:01:16,560
That's both fortunate and unfortunate.
这既是幸运也是不幸。

27
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:18,680
It's the United Nations in my class.
我们班就像联合国一样。

28
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:21,120
We have people from all over the world.
我们有来自世界各地的人。

29
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:28,160
There are three Germans, a Pole, a Scot, two French, an American, a Brazilian, a Chilean,
有三个德国人、一个波兰人、一个苏格兰人、两个法国人、一个美国人、一个巴西人、一个智利人、

30
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:32,080
a New Zealander, though he prefers to call himself a Kiwi.
一个新西兰人，不过他更喜欢称自己为Kiwi。

31
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:33,080
Who else do we have?
还有谁呢？

32
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:39,360
Oh we have a Moroccan, a Tagolese, a Pakistani, and two Indonesians.
哦，我们有一个摩洛哥人、一个多哥人、一个巴基斯坦人和两个印度尼西亚人。

33
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:42,040
That's quite the array of nationalities.
真是各种各样的国籍啊。

34
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:44,960
Everyone in my class is from Asia except me.
我们班上除了我，所有人都来自亚洲。

35
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:55,440
There are a few South Koreans, several Japanese, Malaysian, Thai, Singaporean, Filipino, Kazakhstani,
有几个韩国人、几个日本人、马来西亚人、泰国人、新加坡人、菲律宾人、哈萨克斯坦人，

36
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:57,120
and one Russian.
还有一个俄罗斯人。

37
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,960
Well I think you're pretty lucky actually.
嗯，我觉得你其实挺幸运的。

38
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:01,720
You have the opportunity to learn so much about Asian culture.
你有机会学到很多关于亚洲文化的东西。

39
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:07,160
I guess so but I think it's going to be hard to relate to my classmates especially with
我想是吧，但我觉得和同学们相处会很难，尤其是

40
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,400
the language barrier.
语言障碍。

41
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:11,120
I think I might change classes.
我可能会换班。

42
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,240
Don't stay the course.
别放弃，坚持下去。

43
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:14,960
Your spoken Chinese will be eternally grateful.
你的中文口语会因此受益匪浅的。

44
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:18,280
I bet you it will even surpass mine with all that practice.
我敢打赌，经过这么多练习，它甚至会超过我的中文。

45
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:20,200
I highly doubt it.
我非常怀疑。

46
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:22,200
Your girlfriend is Chinese.
你女朋友是中国人啊。

47
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:30,880
Well there is that, yes.
嗯，这倒是，没错。

48
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:35,620
So the student jokes that their class is kind of like the United Nations.
所以那个学生开玩笑说他们的班有点像联合国。

49
00:02:35,620 --> 00:02:36,620
So it does sound like it.
听起来确实如此。

50
00:02:36,620 --> 00:02:40,200
We have so many different nationalities that we're going to look at them in two groups
我们有这么多不同的国籍，今天我们会把它们分成两组

51
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,360
today.
来看。

52
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:46,000
But the United Nations as you know is a political group that has people from all over the world
但联合国，如你所知，是一个政治组织，有来自世界各地的人

53
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,760
who make decisions about politics and the environment, things like that.
来决策政治和环境之类的事情。

54
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:51,760
That's right.
没错。

55
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:57,800
So why don't we take a look at these nationalities now on Language Takeaway.
那么，我们现在就在“语言小贴士”环节来看看这些国籍吧。

56
00:02:57,800 --> 00:03:00,880
Language Takeaway.
语言小贴士。

57
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:03,080
The first few are from Europe.
前几个来自欧洲。

58
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:05,800
So these are some European nationalities.
所以这些是一些欧洲国籍。

59
00:03:05,800 --> 00:03:07,040
We've got German.
我们有德国人。

60
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:08,240
Where is a German from?
德国人来自哪里？

61
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:10,040
A German is from Germany.
德国人来自德国。

62
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:14,200
Okay, so next to Germany we have another country, Poland.
好的，那么德国旁边是另一个国家，波兰。

63
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:16,320
What do we call a person from Poland?
我们怎么称呼来自波兰的人？

64
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,680
You call that person a Pole.
你称那个人为波兰人。

65
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:22,280
So is this for a woman and a man or is this just one gender?
这是指女性和男性，还是只指一种性别？

66
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,280
Yeah, it's for both.
是的，两者都适用。

67
00:03:23,280 --> 00:03:24,280
Okay, so Pole.
好的，所以是波兰人。

68
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:27,560
Yeah, a girl that's from Poland would be also a Pole.
是的，来自波兰的女孩也是波兰人。

69
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:31,160
Now someone that comes from Scotland on the other hand.
而来自苏格兰的人呢？

70
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:34,520
That would be a Scot or if it's a man, a Scotsman.
那会是苏格兰人，如果是男性，就是Scotsman。

71
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,720
Scotsman, okay.
苏格兰人，好的。

72
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:41,360
Now this is interesting because we are mentioning the nouns of these nationalities like for
这很有趣，因为我们提到了这些国籍的名词，比如

73
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,480
example German.
德国人。

74
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:46,840
Now when we took a look at Pole from Poland, what would be the adjective?
当我们看来自波兰的波兰人时，形容词是什么？

75
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,480
Do I say I am Pole?
我可以说“我是波兰人”吗？

76
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:51,040
I am Polish.
我是波兰的。

77
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:53,680
Or if you want to use the noun, I am a Pole.
或者如果你想用名词，我是波兰人。

78
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:56,000
But the adjective can be used for things as well.
但形容词也可以用于事物。

79
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:59,320
I love to eat Polish sausages.
我喜欢吃波兰香肠。

80
00:03:59,320 --> 00:04:06,480
Or for example or something from Scotland, you can say I love Scottish whiskey.
或者比如来自苏格兰的东西，你可以说我喜欢苏格兰威士忌。

81
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:09,440
Or I love Scottish kilts, those skirts.
或者我喜欢苏格兰短裙，那些裙子。

82
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:11,800
Alright, so that's the adjective.
好了，所以那是形容词。

83
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:18,600
But in the case of France, the country France, we have to say as a noun, he is a Frenchman.
但就法国这个国家而言，作为名词，我们必须说他是法国人。

84
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,400
Okay, and if it's a woman, a Frenchwoman.
好的，如果是女性，就是法国女人。

85
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:25,880
That's right or in the case of an adjective, I love to eat French bread.
没错，或者作为形容词，我喜欢吃法式面包。

86
00:04:25,880 --> 00:04:26,880
Okay.
好的。

87
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:32,040
Now moving on to South America, we took a look at a Brazilian and a Chilean.
现在转到南美洲，我们看了看巴西人和智利人。

88
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:35,440
Okay, so Brazil, Brazilian.
好的，所以巴西，巴西人。

89
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:38,120
In this country, there are many Brazilians.
在这个国家，有很多巴西人。

90
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:45,140
And Chile or Chile as many Americans say, has people called Chileans.
而智利，或者很多美国人说的Chile，那里的人叫智利人。

91
00:04:45,140 --> 00:04:46,140
Some people say Chilean.
有些人说Chilean。

92
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:50,280
So I don't know, I guess the accent varies a little bit.
所以我不知道，我猜口音有点不同。

93
00:04:50,280 --> 00:04:53,000
Now why don't we move back to the other side of the world.
现在我们为什么不回到世界的另一边呢。

94
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,600
We have a New Zealander.
我们有新西兰人。

95
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:57,840
Alright, so many of you have heard of Australia.
好的，你们很多人听说过澳大利亚。

96
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:59,680
Maybe New Zealand is not as famous.
也许新西兰没那么出名。

97
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:02,100
It's a small country near Australia.
它是一个靠近澳大利亚的小国家。

98
00:05:02,100 --> 00:05:05,320
And the people who come from there are called New Zealanders.
来自那里的人被称为新西兰人。

99
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:11,880
It's very hard to say those sometimes, especially when we have to use the adjective New Zealand.
有时候很难说这些词，尤其是当我们必须用形容词“新西兰”的时候。

100
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:12,880
That's right.
没错。

101
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:15,600
So the student said he prefers to call himself a Kiwi.
所以那个学生说他更喜欢称自己为几维鸟。

102
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:20,400
Alright, so Kiwi was a special kind of bird that could only be found in New Zealand.
好的，几维鸟是一种只能在新西兰找到的特殊鸟类。

103
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:24,360
And so this became a very popular symbol for New Zealand.
所以这成了新西兰非常流行的象征。

104
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:27,360
And now people from New Zealand call themselves Kiwis.
现在来自新西兰的人称自己为几维鸟人。

105
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:29,360
