157
00:08:08,360 --> 00:08:14,600
Language Takeaway We're in Asia for this part of today's lesson,
语言要点 今天课程的这一部分我们在亚洲，

158
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:17,520
so we're going to start with a country called Pakistan.
所以我们要从一个叫巴基斯坦的国家开始。

159
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:20,080
What do we call the people from Pakistan?
我们怎么称呼来自巴基斯坦的人？

160
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,480
We say they are Pakistani.
我们说他们是巴基斯坦人。

161
00:08:21,480 --> 00:08:26,160
Okay, so in Chicago, for example, there are many Pakistanis.
好的，比如在芝加哥，就有很多巴基斯坦人。

162
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:31,480
Okay, and moving on to Southeast Asia, we have Indonesians.
好的，接下来到东南亚，我们有印度尼西亚人。

163
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:36,440
All right, Indonesia is the country, and people who come from there are Indonesian.
没错，印度尼西亚是国家，来自那里的人就是印度尼西亚人。

164
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,240
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

165
00:08:38,240 --> 00:08:42,880
Now if we go back to the north part of Asia, we have South Koreans.
现在如果我们回到亚洲北部，我们有韩国人。

166
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:45,600
So we have North and South Korea on our maps.
所以地图上有北韩和南韩。

167
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:50,680
A person from North Korea is North Korean, and a person from South Korea is South Korean.
来自北韩的人是北韩人，来自南韩的人是南韩人。

168
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:55,320
It's kind of like that same structure, American, Brazilian, Korean.
这有点像同样的结构，美国人、巴西人、韩国人。

169
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,320
Very good.
非常好。

170
00:08:56,320 --> 00:09:00,000
And moving to the island of Japan, we have Japanese.
然后到日本这个岛国，我们有日本人。

171
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,000
So this is an adjective.
所以这是一个形容词。

172
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:03,800
We're talking about a Japanese person.
我们在谈论一个日本人。

173
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:04,840
He is Japanese.
他是日本人。

174
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:08,400
Or we can also talk about the food, like sushi is Japanese food.
或者我们也可以谈论食物，比如寿司是日本食物。

175
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,400
That's right.
没错。

176
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:13,680
Okay, moving back to Southeast Asia again, we have Malaysia.
好的，再回到东南亚，我们有马来西亚。

177
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,960
So people from Malaysia are called Malaysian.
所以来自马来西亚的人被称为马来西亚人。

178
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:21,280
Okay, again with this pattern, Malaysian, Korean.
好的，又是这个模式，马来西亚人、韩国人。

179
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,280
That's right.
没错。

180
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:25,480
And I think you say Malaysian food or you say Malay?
我想你是说马来西亚食物还是马来食物？

181
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:27,800
I've heard some people say Malay.
我听过有些人说马来。

182
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:32,640
I've said Malaysian food generally, but Malay I think is one of the languages, and I think
我一般说马来西亚食物，但马来我认为是一种语言，而且也是

183
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:37,800
it's an ethnic group as well, so you can have Malay people in Singapore, for example.
一个族群，所以你可以有马来人，比如在新加坡。

184
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:38,800
Okay.
好的。

185
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:41,880
And actually we have Thai people and Singaporeans.
实际上我们还有泰国人和新加坡人。

186
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:45,120
So we have two countries there, Thailand and Singapore.
所以那里有两个国家，泰国和新加坡。

187
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:50,720
So Thai is the adjective to describe things that come from Thailand.
所以泰是形容词，用来描述来自泰国的事物。

188
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:51,720
It's kind of unusual.
这有点不寻常。

189
00:09:51,720 --> 00:09:55,420
It doesn't fit that pattern that I mentioned, but it's a very important one to remember
它不符合我提到的那个模式，但如果你喜欢吃这个国家的食物，泰国菜，

190
00:09:55,420 --> 00:09:58,440
if you like to eat food from this country, Thai food.
这是一个很重要的要记住的词。

191
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,880
Yeah, excellent food.
是啊，美味的食物。

192
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:04,360
And Singaporean food is also pretty good, and people from Singapore are also called
新加坡食物也相当不错，来自新加坡的人也被称为

193
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,360
Singaporean.
新加坡人。

194
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:07,760
Here we've got a very tricky one.
这里有一个非常棘手的词。

195
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:10,240
We've got the country, the Philippines.
我们有国家，菲律宾。

196
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:12,400
What do you call a person from the Philippines?
你叫来自菲律宾的人什么？

197
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:17,600
So the Philippines is actually spelled P-H-I, like Philippines, right?
所以菲律宾实际上拼写是P-H-I，像菲律宾，对吧？

198
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:21,200
But if somebody is from the Philippines, we say Filipino with an F.
但如果有人来自菲律宾，我们说菲律宾人，用F开头。

199
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,360
All right, Filipino.
好的，菲律宾人。

200
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:27,280
This is interesting, especially for people who are native Spanish speakers because the
这很有趣，特别是对于母语是西班牙语的人来说，因为

201
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:31,400
Philippines was a Spanish colony for a very long time, and so you might hear someone refer
菲律宾曾经是西班牙殖民地很长时间，所以你可能会听到有人自称

202
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,720
to himself as a Filipino.
为菲律宾人。

203
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:34,280
He's a man.
他是男人。

204
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:37,240
Or if she is a woman, a Filipina.
或者如果她是女人，菲律宾女人。

205
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:41,880
So this is very similar to the Spanish structure of having a gender on the end of the word.
所以这非常类似于西班牙语结构，词尾有性别。

206
00:10:41,880 --> 00:10:43,180
That's right.
没错。

207
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:47,400
And well, now we're moving on to Kazakhstan and Russia.
好了，现在我们转到哈萨克斯坦和俄罗斯。

208
00:10:47,400 --> 00:10:52,360
We have people that are from Kazakhstan and Russia, and we say they are Kazakhstani.
我们有来自哈萨克斯坦和俄罗斯的人，我们说他们是哈萨克斯坦人。

209
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:58,400
So this is very common in that part of the world to end the adjective in an I, like Afghanistan,
所以在世界那个地区，以I结尾的形容词很常见，比如阿富汗，

210
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:03,280
Afghani, Pakistan, Pakistani, Kazakhstan, Kazakhstani.
阿富汗人，巴基斯坦，巴基斯坦人，哈萨克斯坦，哈萨克斯坦人。

211
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:07,400
And so these are the stans, the former USSR.
所以这些是斯坦国，前苏联国家。

212
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:11,360
So this is a very important structure to remember, but Russia is pretty easy.
所以这是一个很重要的要记住的结构，但俄罗斯很简单。

213
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:15,600
Yeah, people from Russia, you say they are Russian or you have Russian food.
是啊，来自俄罗斯的人，你说他们是俄罗斯人，或者你有俄罗斯食物。

214
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:17,760
I love Russian food.
我喜欢俄罗斯食物。

215
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:21,640
All right, so we have a lot of different nationalities there.
好的，所以我们有很多不同的国籍。

216
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,520
And obviously we didn't cover all of them.
显然我们没有涵盖所有。

217
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:26,280
I think, I don't know, maybe 200 nationalities.
我想，我不知道，大概200个国籍。

218
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:30,160
So why don't we listen to the dialogue again, and we'll be back to talk a little bit more
所以我们为什么不再次听对话，然后我们会回来多聊一点

219
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,400
about this really interesting topic.
这个非常有趣的话题。

220
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:39,440
Hey, how was your first day of class?
嘿，你第一天上课怎么样？

221
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:42,220
I'm a level two and I'm loving my class this semester.
我是二级班，这学期我很喜欢我的课。

222
00:11:42,220 --> 00:11:46,000
It's great being in a class of international students.
在国际学生班里上课很棒。

223
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:50,280
Mine was okay, except that no one in my class speaks English.
我的课还行，只是班上没人说英语。

224
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:53,560
I guess it will force me to converse in Chinese more in class.
我想这会逼我在课堂上多用中文交流。

225
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:56,600
So at least I should improve a lot this semester.
所以至少这学期我应该进步很多。

226
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:58,840
That's both fortunate and unfortunate.
这既幸运又不幸。

227
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,920
It's the United Nations in my class.
我班上就像联合国一样。

228
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:03,360
We have people from all over the world.
我们有来自世界各地的人。

229
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:10,400
There are three Germans, a Pole, a Scot, two French, an American, a Brazilian, a Chilean,
有三个德国人，一个波兰人，一个苏格兰人，两个法国人，一个美国人，一个巴西人，一个智利人，

230
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:14,320
a New Zealander, though he prefers to call himself a Kiwi.
一个新西兰人，虽然他更喜欢称自己为几维鸟。

231
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,320
Who else do we have?
我们还有谁？

232
00:12:15,320 --> 00:12:21,640
Oh, we have a Moroccan, a Tagolese, a Pakistani, and two Indonesians.
哦，我们有一个摩洛哥人，一个多哥人，一个巴基斯坦人，和两个印度尼西亚人。

233
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:24,320
That's quite the array of nationalities.
真是各种各样的国籍。

234
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:27,240
Everyone in my class is from Asia, except me.
我班上除了我，所有人都是亚洲人。

235
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:37,760
There are a few South Koreans, several Japanese, Malaysian, Thai, Singaporean, Filipino, Kazakhstani,
有几个韩国人，几个日本人，马来西亚人，泰国人，新加坡人，菲律宾人，哈萨克斯坦人，

236
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:38,760
and one Russian.
和一个俄罗斯人。

237
00:12:38,760 --> 00:12:41,280
Well, I think you're pretty lucky, actually.
嗯，我觉得你其实挺幸运的。

238
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:44,040
You have the opportunity to learn so much about Asian culture.
你有机会学到很多关于亚洲文化的东西。

239
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:49,560
I guess so, but I think it's going to be hard to relate to my classmates, especially with
我想是吧，但我觉得很难和同学建立联系，特别是

240
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,720
the language barrier.
有语言障碍。

241
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:52,960
I think I might change classes.
我想我可能要换班了。

242
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:53,960
Don't!
别换！

243
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:54,960
Stay the course.
坚持下去。

244
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:57,240
Your spoken Chinese will be eternally grateful.
你的中文口语会因此感激不尽的。

245
00:12:57,240 --> 00:13:00,560
I bet you it will even surpass mine with all that practice.
我敢打赌，经过这么多练习，它甚至会超过我的水平。

246
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:02,480
I highly doubt it.
我对此深表怀疑。

247
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,560
Your girlfriend is Chinese.
你女朋友是中国人。

248
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:08,040
Well, there is that, yes.
嗯，确实如此。

249
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:11,840
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

250
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:16,360
So talking about nationalities, I think there's one that we didn't mention that's very, very
说到国籍，我觉得有一个我们没提到，而且非常非常

251
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,480
popular.
流行的。

252
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:18,480
People from Ireland.
来自爱尔兰的人。

253
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:22,600
Okay, so people from Ireland are called Irish.
好的，所以来自爱尔兰的人被称为Irish。

254
00:13:22,600 --> 00:13:23,680
Irish.
Irish。

255
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:26,160
The Irish or Irishmen.
爱尔兰人或爱尔兰男人。

256
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:31,520
This is a similar structure to a lot of those countries in Northern Europe like Sweden and
这和很多北欧国家，比如瑞典和

257
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:32,520
Finland.
芬兰，的结构类似。

258
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,520
That's right.
没错。

259
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:36,360
So somebody from Sweden would be called Swedish.
所以来自瑞典的人被称为Swedish。

260
00:13:36,360 --> 00:13:39,080
Yes, or a Swede is the noun.
是的，或者Swede是名词形式。

261
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:42,960
So I love to eat Swedish food like salmon.
所以我喜欢吃瑞典食物，比如三文鱼。

262
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:46,400
But a similar structure applies to Finland.
但类似的结构也适用于芬兰。

263
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:49,360
In Finland, they're very famous for their Finnish bread.
在芬兰，他们的芬兰面包非常有名。

264
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:50,360
Finnish.
Finnish。

265
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:54,240
So that's the way that you say Finnish with double N, right?
所以这就是你读Finnish的方式，双N，对吧？

266
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,240
That's right.
没错。

267
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:56,920
It's not like I finished my homework.
它不像“我完成了作业”里的finished。

268
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:58,400
It's like F-I-N-N-I-S-H.
它是F-I-N-N-I-S-H。

269
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,400
Finnish.
Finnish。

270
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,400
Finnish.
Finnish。

271
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:03,480
And now, what about people from Denmark?
那么，来自丹麦的人呢？

272
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,480
They are Danish.
他们是Danish。

273
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:05,480
Danish.
Danish。

274
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,880
And what about people from Norway?
那来自挪威的人呢？

275
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:09,160
They are Norwegian.
他们是Norwegian。

276
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:11,320
So that's one that does not fit the pattern.
所以这是一个不符合规律的情况。

277
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:15,240
And this is a very interesting one that also doesn't fit the pattern at all.
还有一个非常有趣的，也完全不符合规律。

278
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:16,240
People from Holland.
来自荷兰的人。

279
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:18,880
Okay, so Holland as a country has two names.
好的，所以荷兰这个国家有两个名字。

280
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:20,320
We sometimes say Holland.
我们有时说Holland。

281
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:22,400
We sometimes say the Netherlands.
我们有时说the Netherlands。

282
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:25,000
But a person who comes from Holland is called Dutch.
但来自荷兰的人被称为Dutch。

283
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,080
He is Dutch.
他是Dutch。

284
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:28,080
That's right.
没错。

285
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:33,040
So it doesn't have to do with neither Holland, you don't say a Hollander, or Netherlands,
所以它既和Holland无关，你不会说Hollander，也和Netherlands无关，

286
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:34,160
you don't say Netherlander.
你不会说Netherlander。

287
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:35,160
It's Dutch.
它是Dutch。

288
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,160
Dutch.
Dutch。

289
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:39,160
And you'll also read this on like cookie tins.
你也会在饼干罐上看到这个。

290
00:14:39,160 --> 00:14:41,560
You know, boxes for cookies, Dutch style cookies.
你知道，装饼干的盒子，荷兰式饼干。

291
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:42,560
That's right.
没错。

292
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:44,920
All right, so that's a very important one when it comes to food.
好的，所以在食物方面，这是一个非常重要的词。

293
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:47,480
But we're very curious to hear about where you come from.
但我们非常好奇你来自哪里。

294
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:50,520
You should try some of the new vocabulary words that we have introduced here.
你应该试试我们这里介绍的一些新词汇。

295
00:14:50,520 --> 00:14:52,400
Talk about your friends or your family.
聊聊你的朋友或家人。

296
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:56,040
But also, tell us if we didn't include your nationality.
另外，如果我们没有提到你的国籍，也请告诉我们。

297
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:57,040
That's right.
没错。

298
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,040
All right, so we'll see you guys there.
好的，那我们就在那里见。

299
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,040
EnglishPod.com.
EnglishPod.com。

300
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:07,240
Enjoy your meal!
请享用你的餐点！
